-virtual-pixel <method>
specify contents of "virtual pixels"
This option defines "virtual pixels" for use in operations that can access
pixels outside the boundaries of an image.
Choose from these methods:
ConstantUse the image background color.EdgeExtend the edge pixel toward infinity
(default).MirrorMirror the image.TileTile the image.
This option affects operations that use virtual pixels such as -blur, -sharpen,
-wave, etc.
